data.chText: 抗议；抗议书（或行动）；反对
data.enText: the expression of strong disagreement with or opposition to sth; a statement or an action that shows this

data.chText: 主任辞职以示抗议这项决定。
data.enText: The director resigned in protest at the decision.

data.chText: 这个声明引起了一场抗议风潮。
data.enText: The announcement raised a storm of protest .

data.chText: 抗议游行
data.enText: a protest march

data.chText: 她一声未吭地接受了指控。
data.enText: She accepted the charge without protest .

data.chText: 工人们进行抗议，反对拟议中的对他们合同的修改。
data.enText: The workers staged a protest against the proposed changes in their contracts.

data.chText: 尽管当地居民反对，建筑工程将照样进行。
data.enText: The building work will go ahead, despite protests from local residents.

data.chText: 暴乱是从一场和平抗议开始的。
data.enText: The riot began as a peaceful protest.
under protest

data.chText: 无奈地；不服气地；不甘心地
data.enText: unwillingly and after expressing disagreement

data.chText: 她无奈之下写了一封致歉信。
data.enText: She wrote a letter of apology but only under protest.

data.chText: （公开）反对；抗议
data.enText: to say or do sth to show that you disagree with or disapprove of sth, especially publicly

data.chText: 学生们走上街头，抗议这项决定。
data.enText: Students took to the streets to protest against the decision.

data.chText: 受害人的遗孀抗议判决太轻。
data.enText: The victim's widow protested at the leniency of the sentence.

data.chText: 抗议没有用，我决不改变主意。
data.enText: There's no use protesting, I won't change my mind.

data.chText: 他们决意反对这项决定。
data.enText: They fully intend to protest the decision.

data.chText: 坚决地表示；申辩
data.enText: to say firmly that sth is true, especially when you have been accused of sth or when other people do not believe you

data.chText: 她一直坚持说自己是无辜的。
data.enText: She has always protested her innocence .

data.chText: 他坚持说路途太远，不宜开汽车去。
data.enText: He protested that the journey was too far by car.

data.chText: “你当初不是这么说的！”简争辩说。
data.enText: ‘That's not what you said earlier!’ Jane protested.

data.text: complain ♦ protest ♦ object ♦ grumble ♦ moan ♦ whine ♦ whinge

data.chText: 以上各词均含对人或事物感到恼怒、不高兴或不满之义。
data.enText: These words all mean to say that you are annoyed, unhappy or not satisfied about sb/sth.
complain

data.chText: 指抱怨、埋怨、发牢骚：
data.enText: to say that you are annoyed, unhappy or not satisfied about sb/sth

data.chText: 我要就这件事给经理提意见。
data.enText: I'm going to complain to the manager about this.
protest

data.chText: 指公开反对、抗议或申辩：
data.enText: to say or do sth to show that you disagree with or disapprove of sth, especially publicly; to give sth as a reason for protesting

data.chText: 学生走上街头抗议这项决定。
data.enText: Students took to the streets to protest against the decision.
object

data.chText: 指不同意、不赞成、反对或抗辩：
data.enText: to say that you disagree with or disapprove of sth; to give sth as a reason for objecting

data.chText: 如果没有人反对，我们就把会议推迟到下周。
data.enText: If nobody objects, we'll postpone the meeting till next week.

data.chText: 他抗辩说警察没有充分证据就逮捕了他。
data.enText: He objected that the police had arrested him without sufficient evidence.
grumble

data.chText: 指咕哝、嘟囔、发牢骚：
data.enText: ( rather informal , disapproving ) to complain about sb/sth in a bad-tempered way

data.chText: 他们不停地嘟囔着说冷。
data.enText: They kept grumbling that they were cold.
moan

data.chText: 指抱怨、埋怨：
data.enText: ( BrE , rather informal , disapproving ) to complain about sb/sth in an annoying way

data.chText: 你在抱怨什么呢？
data.enText: What are you moaning on about now?
whine

data.chText: 指哭哭啼啼或哭嚷着诉说：
data.enText: ( rather informal , disapproving ) to complain in an annoying, crying voice

data.chText: 别哭哭啼啼的！
data.enText: Stop whining!

data.chText: “我要回家。”托比哼哼唧唧地说。
data.enText: ‘I want to go home,’ whined Toby.

data.chText: whine通常用于小孩子抱怨。
data.enText: Whine is often used to talk about the way that young children complain.
whinge

data.chText: 指絮絮叨叨地抱怨：
data.enText: ( BrE , informal , disapproving ) to complain about sb/sth in an annoying way

data.chText: 她总是嘟囔着说一切都太不公平了。
data.enText: She's always whingeing about how unfair everything is.

data.chText: 用grumble、moan还是whinge？
以上三词均为complain的非正式用词。grumble表达抱怨者的感受，即心情不好；moan和whinge多表达听者的心情，即抱怨使人心烦。
data.enText: These are all fairly informal words for ‘complain’. Grumble tells you how the person who is complaining feels (= they are in a bad mood) ; moan and whinge tell you more about how the people listening to the complaints feel (= the complaining is annoying them) .
grumble, moan or whinge ?
to complain/protest/grumble/moan/whine/whinge about sth
to complain/protest/grumble/moan at sth
to complain/protest/object/grumble/moan/whine/whinge to sb
to complain/protest/object/grumble/moan/whine that…
to complain/protest/object bitterly

simple_means.memory_skill: pro 在前 + test 测试；证据 → 在前面论证 → 坚决声明 → 引申为表示抗议

ex.chText: 如果没人反对的话，该计划将立即执行。
ex.enText: If no one objects, the plan will be implemented immediately.

ex.chText: 她坚决反对重建该寺庙。
ex.enText: She strongly objected to rebuilding the temple.

ex.chText: 她不赞成聘用那个男人。
ex.enText: She objected to recruiting that man.

synonyms.bx: 语气强烈，指对某一具体做法、计划等表示反对，常后接介词 to。

ex.chText: 我不反对你的计划。
ex.enText: I have no objection to your plan.

tips.tip: 在表示“不反对…”时，习惯上用 have no objection to，而不用 do not object to。

ex.chText: 经济学家对通货膨胀的原因看法不一。
ex.enText: Economists differ on the cause of inflation.

ex.chText: 他总是与她意见相左。
ex.enText: He always differs with her.

ex.chText: 在这件事上我和你意见不同。
ex.enText: I disagree with you on this matter.

ex.chText: 即便是亲密的朋友有时也有分歧。
ex.enText: Even close friends disagree sometimes.

ex.chText: 有些人不同意他的论点。
ex.enText: Some people disagree with his argument.

synonyms.bx: 指与他人在看法上有分歧，也指不赞同计划、行动等，语气较differ 强烈，常后接介词 with。

ex.chText: 国会会继续反对总统的经济紧缩措施吗？
ex.enText: Will the Congress continue to oppose the President's austerity measures?

ex.chText: 委员会反对改变规则。
ex.enText: The committee opposed changing the regulations.

ex.chText: 当地居民强烈反对这个计划。
ex.enText: The local residents bitterly opposed the scheme.

ex.chText: 我们反对任何外来势力插手干预。
ex.enText: We oppose interference by any outside force.

synonyms.bx: 指不赞同某一政策、计划等，含抵制或阻挠之意。

ex.chText: 成千上万的人走上街头，抗议经济紧缩政策。
ex.enText: Tens of thousands of people took to the streets, protesting against the austerity policy.

ex.chText: 许多学生反对那项决定。
ex.enText: Many students protested the decision.

ex.chText: 数千人抗议新法规。
ex.enText: Thousands of people protested against the new legislation.

ex.chText: “我不明白为什么他会升职！”她抗议道。
ex.enText: 'I don't see why he should get the promotion!' she protested.

synonyms.bx: 通常指人们聚集在一起，以言语、行为等公开表示不满或异议，也可指个人不认同某事或对某事心有不满。

ex.chText: 那位部长顶住了要求其辞职的压力。
ex.enText: The minister resisted pressure to resign.

ex.chText: 为什么该计划遭到董事会的强烈反对？
ex.enText: Why was the plan fiercely resisted by the board?

ex.chText: 该公司拒绝改变聘用制度。
ex.enText: The company resisted changing its recruitment system.

synonyms.bx: 指拒绝作出改变或不屈从于外力而做某事。

data.enText: unwillingly and after expressing disagreement

data.chText: 她无奈之下写了一封致歉信。
data.enText: She wrote a letter of apology but only under protest.

tr: a public (often organized) manifestation of dissent
a formal and solemn declaration of objection
example: they finished the game under protest to the league president
the senator rose to register his protest
the many protestations did not stay the execution

tr: the act of making a strong public expression of disagreement and disapproval
example: he shouted his protests at the umpire
a shower of protest was heard from the rear of the hall

tr: affirm or avow formally or solemnly
express opposition through action or words
example: dissent to the laws of the country

value.boxr_value: The verb is pronounced /prə'test/. The noun is pronounced /'prəʊtest/. 动词读作 /prə'test/，名词读作 /'prəʊtest/。

value.def: If you protest against something or about something, you say or show publicly that you object to it. In American English, you usually say that you protest it.

example.ex: Groups of women took to the streets to  protest against the arrests...
example.tran: 成群结队的妇女上街抗议逮捕行动。

example.ex: The students were protesting at overcrowding in the university hostels...
example.tran: 学生们在抗议大学宿舍过于拥挤。

example.ex: He picked up the cat before Rosa could protest.
example.tran: 未等罗莎表示异议，他就抱起了猫。

value.def: A protest is the act of saying or showing publicly that you object to something.

example.ex: The opposition now seems too weak to stage any serious protests against the government...
example.tran: 反对党现在似乎势力非常弱小，无法针对政府发起真正的抗议。

example.ex: The unions called a two-hour strike in protest at the railway authority's announcement.
example.tran: 各工会号召罢工两小时，以对铁路当局所发通告表示抗议。

value.def: If you protest that something is the case, you insist that it is the case, when other people think that it may not be.

example.ex: When we tried to protest that Mo was beaten up they didn't believe us...
example.tran: 我们试图申明莫遭到了毒打，他们却不相信我们。

example.ex: 'I never said any of that to her,' he protested...
example.tran: “我从来没有对她那么说过，”他申辩道。

example.ex: He has always protested his innocence.
example.tran: 他一直申辩自己是无辜的。

value.def: A protest that something is true is a strong declaration that it is true.

example.ex: That was how she usually dealt with their protests that she was spoiling her grandchildren.
example.tran: 当他们坚持说她是在溺爱孙儿，她通常会作出那样的回应。

trans: 无异议，在“不保留异议”的情况下
抗议中；在抗议下；在抗议下签字；不情愿地

con 共同 + test 测试；证据 → 共同论证 → 争论
contest 竞赛；争论 + ant 表人 → 竞争者
de 去掉，取消 + test 测试；证据 → 不愿〔出面〕作证 → 憎恶
pro 在前 + test 测试；证据 → 在前面论证 → 坚决声明 → 引申为表示抗议
testi 测试；证据 + fy 使… → 用证据证明 → 证实
testi 测试；证据 + mon 提醒 + ial …的 → 供提醒的证据 → 证明书
testi 测试；证据 + mony 表结果、状态 → 证据；证词
